<plot>In the midst of a technology company's bankruptcy, the employees are on the verge of revolt. Glen (Brian Slaten) decides to take matters into his own hands by stealing the company's confidential customer data. Roger (John Nutten) is a headhunter who acts as a middleman in the sale of the data to a competitor. A plan is hatched to steal the entire database and frame it on Dave (Brad Fleischer), a sleazy co-worker. Not only does the plan go awry, but Dave learns of the deception and turns the tables around to blackmail Glen. Tension mounts even further as the two men jockey for leverage over each other and over the receptionist (Katherine Sigismund) who has gotten sucked into the intrigue.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?334090</url></doc>
